From c7cf81a2b0cfce1fdcef2ae91863d762de46c49f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Ritesh Harjani (IBM)" <ritesh.list@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 16 May 2025 01:20:50 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 06/16] ext4: Check if inode uses extents in
 ext4_inode_can_atomic_write()
Git-commit: 1c972b1d13dde34c9897d991283e2c54209b44e9
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: jsc#PED-15653

EXT4 only supports doing atomic write on inodes which uses extents, so
add a check in ext4_inode_can_atomic_write() which gets called during
open.

Reviewed-by: Ojaswin Mujoo <ojaswin@linux.ibm.com>
Acked-by: Darrick J. Wong <djwong@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Ritesh Harjani (IBM) <ritesh.list@gmail.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/86bb502c979398a736ab371d8f35f6866a477f6c.1747337952.git.ritesh.list@gmail.com
Signed-off-by: Theodore Ts'o <tytso@mit.edu>
Acked-by: David Disseldorp <ddiss@suse.de>

---
 fs/ext4/ext4.h | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/ext4/ext4.h b/fs/ext4/ext4.h
index a11c0bbb86cda..2504acaa0884e 100644
--- a/fs/ext4/ext4.h
+++ b/fs/ext4/ext4.h
@@ -3881,7 +3881,9 @@ static inline int ext4_buffer_uptodate(struct buffer_head *bh)
 static inline bool ext4_inode_can_atomic_write(struct inode *inode)
 {
 
-	return S_ISREG(inode->i_mode) && EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb)->s_awu_min > 0;
+	return S_ISREG(inode->i_mode) &&
+		ext4_test_inode_flag(inode, EXT4_INODE_EXTENTS) &&
+		EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb)->s_awu_min > 0;
 }
 
 extern int ext4_block_write_begin(handle_t *handle, struct folio *folio,
-- 
